The paper proposes a novel replication scheme for highly dependable services, which involves combining two replication schemes: deferred update mode and state machine mode. The paper also discusses the development and evaluation of a distributed transactional memory system. Based on this, the most likely sub-categories are cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing), cs.DB (Databases), cs.OS (Operating Systems), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), and cs.PL (Programming Languages).
